$ git config --list      // List the current configuration of git CLI
$ git config --global --user.name "<user name>"  // Set username
$ git config --global --user.email "xyz@gmail.com"    // set email ID
$ git init      // Initialized a empty git repository
$ git status            // Show status of the git repo
$ git add <file name>      // add files to staging area
$ git add .              // add all modified/untracked files to staging area from current directory
$ git commit -m "commit message"        // commit all staged files
$ git restore --staged <file name>      // Remove file from staging area
$ git rm                   // delete/remove file from git repo

## How to restore a deleted file from git repo
$ git restore --staged <file name>
$ git restore <file name> 
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
$ git log                   // show git logs
$ git log --oneline        // show only commit ID and commit message on single line
$ git log -n                // show first n number of commits
